Oxygen ordering in the high-T$_c$ superconductor HgBa$_2$CaCu$_2$O$_{6+\delta}$ as revealed by perturbed angular correlation / Mendonca, Tania Melo (Neel Lab, Grenoble ; Porto U.) ; Correia, Joao Guilherme (ITN, Sacavem ; Lisbon U., CFNUL) ; Haas, Heinz (ITN, Sacavem) ; Odier, Philippe (Neel Lab, Grenoble) ; Tavares, Pedro (UTAD, Vila Real) ; Silva, Manuel Ribeiro (Lisbon U., CFNUL) ; Lopes, Armandina (Lisbon U., CFNUL) ; Pereira, Andre (Porto U.) ; Goncalves, Joao Nuno (U. Aveiro) ; Amaral, Joao (U. Aveiro) et al. 
Lattice sites and collective ordering of oxygen atoms in HgBa$_2$CaCu$_2$O$_{6+\delta}$ were studied using the perturbed angular correlation (PAC) technique at ISOLDE/CERN. The electric field gradients (EFG) at 199mHg nuclei have been measured as functions of oxygen doping on the Hg planes, above and below T$_c$. [...] 
CERN-OPEN-2014-022.- Geneva : CERN, 2011 - 10 p. \- Published in : Phys. Rev. B 84 (2011) 094524 Preprint: PDF;

Perturbed Angular Correlations Studies in the HgBa$_2$CaCu$_2$O$_{6+\delta}$ high-T$_c$ Superconductor / Mendonca, Tania Melo (Porto U.) ; Correia, Joao Guilherme (ITN, Sacavem) ; Haas, Heinz (ITN, Sacavem) ; Odier, Philippe (Neel Lab, Grenoble) ; Tavares, Pedro (UTAD, Vila Real) ; SIlva, Manuel Ribeiro (Lisbon U., CFNUL) ; Lopes, Armandina (Lisbon U., CFNUL) ; Darie, Celine (Neel Lab, Grenoble) ; Araujo, Joao Pedro (Porto U.) 
The electric field gradients at $^{199m}$Hg nuclei have been measured via the perturbed angular correlation (PAC) technique, allowing a full characterization of the Hg neighborhood charge distribution at high oxygen doping on the Hg planes. The PAC technique has been applied to investigate the effect of high oxygen pressure during the measurement. [...] 
CERN-OPEN-2014-021.- Geneva : CERN, 2011 - 4 p. \- Published in : J. Supercond. Novel Magn. 24 (2011) 1153-1156 Preprint: PDF;

Perturbed angular correlations investigations on YMnO3 multiferroic manganite / Mendonca, Tania Melo (Porto U.) ; Lopes, Armandina (Lisbon U., CFNUL) ; Goncalves, Joao Nuno (U. Aveiro) ; Correia, Joao (ITN, Sacavem) ; Tavares, Pedro (UTAD, Vila Real) ; Amaral, Vitor (U. Aveiro) ; Daries, Celine (Neel Lab, Grenoble) ; Araujo, Joao Pedro (Porto U.) 
The Perturbed Angular Correlation (PAC) technique was applied to study the yttrium local environment in YMnO$_3$ multiferroic manganite. The electric field gradients (EFG) at the Y site have been measured as function of temperature, covering both ferroelectric and magnetic transitions. [...] 
